			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kind of late on this reply, but it's worth noting...
<br />

<br />
When you have the "others hits" filter on, which shows hits for all the stuff thats near you, it basically turns off the "pet hits" because they're already being reported by the "others hits" filter. Most likely, for spam purposes, the range on "others hits" is not nearly as big as just the pet hits.
<br />

<br />
The same goes for "others misses" so I'm betting that you had your "others hits" filter off and your "others misses" filter on.... making your pet hits out of range and your misses within range.
<br />

<br />
So it's not even really a bug... it's just inconsistant coding. Nothing to be suprised about, really.<br />_________________<br />Ouen Quen
<br />
Magician and Scholar
<br />
Firionia Vie</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
